==English==
===Etymology===
From the name of the manufacturer of water carts, manufactured in Shepparton, Victoria.  The meaning derives - as it does for [[scuttle butt]] - from the sort of talk that went on around the water cart.
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''furphy'''
#(''Australian slang'') a [[rumour]], or an [[erroneous]] or [[improbable]] [[story]].
